\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to define the internal organizational structure,
 operational scope,
 behavioral expectations,
 and advancement pathways for all personnel within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 It establishes a formal hierarchy of authority,
 accountability,
 and technical competency aligned with industry frameworks to ensure the consistent delivery of technology services and the security of County information assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations personnel,
 including full-time employees,
 part-time staff,
 trainees,
 contractors,
 and temporary workers.
 It governs internal role design,
 authority delegation,
 support escalation,
 and professional development expectations.
\end_layout

