\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Role Tier Structure & Security Clearance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Information Operations Department is organized into hierarchical role tiers to ensure operational clarity,
 escalation discipline,
 and professional development.
 Role tiers L0–L5 correspond directly to the roles defined in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Workforce Roles STAK Matrix).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Security Screening Requirements
\series default
:
 Assignment of any individual,
 including contractors and temporary personnel,
 to a role above "Trainee" is contingent upon the successful adjudication of background screening required for that tier as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Personnel Security).
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Rescreening
\series default
:
 Personnel with access to Criminal Justice Information (CJI) shall undergo rescreening at least once every five (5) years in accordance with 
\series bold
CJIS Security Policy Section 5.12
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Advancement
\series default
:
 Advancement between tiers shall require verification that the individual's background screening adjudication remains current and appropriate for the target tier's access level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Competency Maintenance and Privileged Access Eligibility
\series default
:
 Assignment to Tier L3 (Administrator) and above is contingent upon maintaining the current,
 valid role requirements designated as mandatory in 
\series bold
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "app:6.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Workforce Roles STAK Matrix) and the Departmental Career Ladder,
 including any required certifications and renewals where specified.
 A lapse in a mandatory requirement (e.g.,
 expiration,
 revocation,
 or failure to maintain renewal status) shall result in the immediate suspension of administrative privileges and removal from unsupervised Tier L3+ duties.
 The individual shall be temporarily reassigned to Tier L2 duties (Support Specialist) or lower until the requirement is reinstated or a written exception is approved by the IT Director in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 All suspensions,
 exceptions,
 and reinstatements shall be documented in the Department’s system of record and managed under the corrective action framework in 
