\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Advancement Pathways
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Advancement within the Department is meritocratic,
 earned through demonstrated competency mastery,
 certification acquisition,
 and cultural adherence.
 Tenure alone shall not constitute grounds for promotion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Criteria
\series default
:
 Advancement decisions shall consider both technical competency and security compliance history (e.g.,
 adherence to policies,
 absence of unresolved disciplinary actions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Pathways
\series default
:
 Specific criteria for advancement from Trainee,
 Support Specialist,
 and Administrator roles are defined in the Departmental Career Ladder and aligned with the STAK Matrix.
\end_layout

